Pneumonia:

• Pneumonia refers to inflammation of the lungs
• In this condition the body temperature increases over 40.6°C (105.1° F)

Symptoms to look for:

• High fever
• Difficulty in breathing
• Sharp pain in chest
• Cough accompanied with pink mucus
• Pulse rate rises over 150 beats per minute
• Delirium and convulsions in children

Causes:

• Contact with germs
• Fungal infection
• Irritation by worms
• Inhaling foreign matter or toxic gases
• Unhealthy eating habits

